result.execSummary:
The defendant Rodolfo T Villarreal was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery by Prisoners, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.20(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Statutory costs assessed.   If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

No alcohol or controlled substances except by prescription. Random UA's are authorized. Any counseling deemed appropriate by agent; specifically anger management and cognitive thinking. No contact with any members of the Gangster Disciples. Must obtain and maintain full time verifiable employment or attend school full time or a combination of both equal to full time. Must attend every class unless defendant has doctor's excuse. Must not be disruptive in class or in hallways. Must do all assignments to the best of his ability. Must get GED or HSED.   Defendant must submit a DNA sample as required by law and pay mandatory DNA surcharge. Firearm warning given. Voting is prohibited until sentence is complete and civil rights have been restored. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations while on supervision.

timeConds.notes: Huber is granted for employment and school. Do not report late or under the influence of alcohol or controlled substances.  Absolute sobriety is required.

Defendant Rodolfo T Villarreal in court with attorney Michelle Marie Anderson.  Defendant Rodolfo T Villarreal in custody.  Robert Scott Repischak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter: Patricia Schaefer.
The State indicates that they had a number of witnesses that had to be located and the victim needed to be located by investigator. The victim was located on July 6 and the victim indicated that they were not sure they wanted to cooperate. The State send a subpoena to the new address for victim. The State indictes they are seriously doubtful that they can go forward with trial on 7/21 and makes an oral motion to adj. written motion to follow. Defense wishes to have this matter tried as soon as possible and they are ready proceed. The defense withdraws the alibi notice as a defense for trial. If the victim wishes to cooperate, the State would be ready to go.

Ms. Anderson files pretrial motions today. Defense MIL will be granted. Turning over prior records will be granted save rebuttal. No Daubert issues and the matter should take a day to a day and a half. No alternate. Preliminary ins put on the record. Ludwig hearing will be done prior to voir dire.

BTC: Matter remains set for trial.
